FBIS4-67105 "jptdd020__l94090" JPRS-TDD-94-020-L JPRS Narcotics 7 May 1994 NEAR EAST & SOUTH ASIA REGIONAL AFFAIRS Pakistani Interior Minister Cited on Antidrug Accord With Pakistani Interior Minister Cited on Antidrug Accord With Iran BK0705091094 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 GMT 7 May 94 BK0705091094 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network Urdu BFN [Text] Retired Major General Nasirullah Khan Babar, minister of the interior, says the present government is determined to eliminate the drug menace from society. He said this while talking to reporters at Peshawar's airport upon his return from Tehran, where he signed a memorandum of understanding among Iran, Pakistan, and the United Nations Narcotics Control Program. He said the three sides will spend $31 million on narcotics control measures. The interior minister said narcotics are reaching Pakistan from Afghanistan because of the political instability there, while materials used to process heroin are being smuggled into Pakistan from India. During his stay in Tehran, Nasirullah Khan Babar met Iranian President 'Ali Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani and conveyed messages of goodwill and good wishes to him from Pakistan's president and prime minister.
